WEBVTT

00:02.768 --> 00:05.336
¶ Boy, the way
Glenn Miller played ¶

00:05.404 --> 00:09.040
¶ songs that made
the hit parade ¶

00:09.108 --> 00:12.644
¶ guys like us
we had it made ¶

00:12.712 --> 00:15.446
[ together ]
¶ those were the days ¶

00:15.514 --> 00:19.183
<i>¶ and you knew</i>
<i> </i> <i>where you were then ¶</i>

00:19.251 --> 00:23.287
[ Archie ]
¶ girls were girls
and men were men ¶

00:23.355 --> 00:25.724
[ Archie, Edith ]
¶ mister, we could use a man ¶

00:25.791 --> 00:29.560
¶ like Herbert hoover again ¶

00:29.629 --> 00:32.931
[ Archie ]
¶ didn't need no welfare state ¶

00:32.999 --> 00:36.434
[ Edith ]
¶ everybody pulled his weight ¶

00:36.502 --> 00:40.138
[ Archie, Edith ]
¶ gee, our old lasalle
ran great ¶

00:40.205 --> 00:44.643
¶ those were the days ¶

00:52.584 --> 00:56.021
¶ don't sit under
the apple tree ¶

00:56.088 --> 00:58.256
¶ with anybody else but me ¶

00:58.323 --> 01:00.491
¶ no, no, no, no, no ¶

01:00.559 --> 01:02.794
¶ with anybody else but me ¶

01:02.862 --> 01:06.031
¶ no, no, no, no, no, no ¶

01:06.098 --> 01:09.734
- ¶ with anybody else but me
no, no ¶
- Michael?

01:09.802 --> 01:11.770
Hey, ma,
have you seen Michael?

01:11.837 --> 01:14.238
Oh, Gloria,
you won't believe this.

01:14.306 --> 01:17.208
He and Archie
went out together.

01:17.276 --> 01:21.379
Mother, no.
Without adult supervision?
[ Chuckling ]

01:21.446 --> 01:24.415
Archie was out of cigars,
and he asked Mike...

01:24.483 --> 01:27.218
To take a walk with him
down to the store.

01:27.286 --> 01:29.688
Oh, Gloria,
it was wonderful.

01:29.755 --> 01:31.690
Archie was laughing.

01:31.757 --> 01:36.094
And he said he was taking a walk
with his favorite son-in-law.

01:36.162 --> 01:38.063
Daddy said that?

01:38.130 --> 01:41.632
And it's all thanks
to pee wee Reese.

01:43.803 --> 01:47.706
Who's pee wee Reese?
Oh, some football player.

01:49.141 --> 01:54.412
I think they called him pee wee
because he was a short stop.

01:56.215 --> 01:59.450
No, ma, that's "shortstop."
So the game was baseball.

01:59.518 --> 02:03.955
Oh, well, anyway,
Archie was having an argument
with Mr. mcnab...

02:04.023 --> 02:07.625
About who was
the best shortstop ever,

02:07.693 --> 02:11.730
and Mike said
that mcnab was wrong
and Archie was right,

02:11.797 --> 02:14.365
and that was the start
of a beautiful friendship.

02:14.433 --> 02:17.769
That's great,
but I wonder how long
it's gonna last.

02:22.708 --> 02:24.642
Keep away from me, meathead.

02:24.710 --> 02:27.411
Shutting the door in my face
is not gonna change things.

02:27.479 --> 02:30.448
Shutting the mouth
in your face might help.

02:30.515 --> 02:32.250
All right.
What's happened?

02:32.317 --> 02:35.019
What happened?
You wanna know what happened?
He saw what happened.

02:35.087 --> 02:37.355
I didn't see nothing.
Now stay off my back.

02:37.422 --> 02:40.625
How would you like it
if you were Tony?
Well, I ain't Tony.

02:40.692 --> 02:42.927
Tony who?
Tony vicino.

02:42.995 --> 02:46.965
The shoemaker? I thought
you went out to get cigars.

02:47.032 --> 02:49.834
That's right.
I went out just to do
a little peaceful shopping.

02:49.902 --> 02:52.403
With your favorite son-in-law.

02:52.471 --> 02:54.806
Stifle that.

02:54.874 --> 02:57.008
Why don't you admit it?
You saw it.

02:57.076 --> 02:59.778
I didn't see no muggin'.

02:59.845 --> 03:01.913
Tony mugged somebody?

03:01.981 --> 03:05.349
No, Edith.
Tony wasn't the mugger.
He was the "muggee."

03:05.417 --> 03:09.854
Yeah. Yeah,
and Archie was right there,
and he says he didn't see it.

03:09.922 --> 03:13.524
Archie, it is your duty
as a citizen to come forward
and be a witness.

03:13.592 --> 03:16.294
That's okay for students
and the unemployed,

03:16.361 --> 03:20.064
which in your case
is one and the same thing.

03:20.132 --> 03:24.535
I happen to be a working man.
I don't get paid if
I turn up for work absent.

03:24.603 --> 03:28.072
Oh, you hear that reasoning?
"I'll do the right thing
if they pay me."

03:28.140 --> 03:31.109
If you're a witness
in one of these things,
you know what you gotta do?

03:31.177 --> 03:33.178
Put on a shirt and tie.
You gotta go down to court,

03:33.245 --> 03:36.181
wait for that case
to be called up,
which who knows when.

03:36.248 --> 03:38.983
Then by the time it gets
called up, you forget
what you was gonna say,

03:39.051 --> 03:42.486
some lawyer makes a monkey
out of you, and it all
goes down on your record.

03:42.554 --> 03:45.089
So because of
a little inconvenience,
you don't want to get involved.

03:45.157 --> 03:48.392
Listen, let me explain something
to you, huh? Shut up!

03:48.460 --> 03:51.462
You hear that, Gloria?
What are you looking at?

03:51.530 --> 03:53.531
You see? That's how he
settles everything.

03:53.598 --> 03:57.268
Michael, calm down.
We don't know what's going on.
Tell us what happened.

03:57.336 --> 03:59.637
Archie and I
went into the deli--
just a minute.

03:59.705 --> 04:01.605
I'll tell it.
You better tell the truth.

04:01.673 --> 04:03.774
Forget the truth.
Listen to me.

04:05.845 --> 04:07.778
The two of us went down
to the deli, see?

04:07.847 --> 04:10.481
To get that six-pack
and some cigars for me.

04:10.549 --> 04:14.585
Now, this guy is yapping
so much about baseball
that I leave the shop,

04:14.653 --> 04:17.856
and I'm halfway down
the street, and I see
I'm all out of cigars.

04:17.923 --> 04:20.892
I left them on the counter
back there.
So I ran back to get them.

04:20.959 --> 04:24.095
Will you
let me tell the story?

04:24.163 --> 04:27.098
So he runs back to get them.

04:27.166 --> 04:29.868
So I'm standing there
on the street,
and all of a sudden, someone--

04:29.935 --> 04:33.104
I don't know who--
jumps Tony vicino,
the shoemaker,

04:33.172 --> 04:36.207
when he's closing up
his little joint
and steals his cash box.

04:36.275 --> 04:41.179
- Now, that's the story.
- Except that Archie was there,
and he saw the whole thing.

04:41.247 --> 04:44.448
Listen, my being there
don't prove nothing.

04:44.516 --> 04:46.450
I was in Italy during the war.

04:46.518 --> 04:48.786
That don't mean
I seen mussolini.

04:50.722 --> 04:53.758
That's right.

04:53.825 --> 04:57.828
Archie would've told us
if he'd seen mussolini.

05:01.433 --> 05:03.201
Don't help me, huh, Edith?

05:03.269 --> 05:06.637
Aren't you always the one
who's saying that
it's a jungle out there?

05:06.705 --> 05:09.640
It's gonna get worse
until somebody stands up
and says, "I saw."

05:09.708 --> 05:12.310
How can you be so certain
daddy saw the mugging?

05:12.378 --> 05:14.345
Will you stay out
of this, please?
Hold it.

05:14.413 --> 05:17.282
She's making sense.
A man ought to listen
to his wife.

05:17.349 --> 05:20.084
- Archie--
- dry up.

05:21.820 --> 05:23.888
Archie, you know you saw it!

05:23.956 --> 05:28.126
How do you know what I know?
You don't even know
what you know, schoolboy.

05:28.193 --> 05:31.062
That's what makes you
a meathead!
And you're a dumb polack!

05:31.130 --> 05:33.131
Huh?
Huh? You see?

05:33.198 --> 05:35.866
How does it feel when
the shoe's on the other foot?
Not too good, huh?

05:35.935 --> 05:37.868
You don't like it, huh?
It bothers you, huh?

05:37.937 --> 05:40.038
Well, you're a dumb polack!
[ Forced laughter ]

05:44.576 --> 05:47.211
You belong in a rubber room.

05:48.747 --> 05:50.681
He's sick.
You better put him to bed.

05:50.749 --> 05:52.683
Did you hear that?
Let me out of here.

05:52.751 --> 05:55.353
Archie,
what is this all about?

05:55.421 --> 05:57.455
Did you ever hear anything
like that in your life?

05:57.522 --> 06:00.758
Yeah, lots of times,
right here.

06:00.826 --> 06:02.793
He must've
learned it from you.

06:02.861 --> 06:04.996
Now, you stifle yourself.

06:05.064 --> 06:08.099
He's got some
hell of a nerve telling me
that I gotta be a witness.

06:08.167 --> 06:11.035
You can't be a witness
if you didn't see nothing.

06:11.103 --> 06:13.704
That's it, Edith. That's it.
Thank you very much.

06:13.772 --> 06:17.141
You're welcome, Archie.
But if you did see something--

06:17.209 --> 06:20.578
now, wait a minute.
Whose side are you
gonna be on?

06:20.645 --> 06:24.715
Yours, Archie. I know
you'll do the right thing.

06:24.783 --> 06:28.353
Just ask yourself,
what do you feel in your heart?

06:28.420 --> 06:30.855
Heartburn, Edith!

06:30.922 --> 06:33.757
Now find me some
bicarbonate soda.
Right away.

06:33.825 --> 06:36.961
I don't care
what you say, Michael.
It was a rotten thing to do.

06:37.029 --> 06:40.131
I'm sorry, all right?
I shouldn't have
said that to his face.

06:40.199 --> 06:42.867
- It was stupid
and uncalled-for.
- All right!

06:42.934 --> 06:45.036
I said I was sorry.
What more do you want?

06:45.104 --> 06:49.440
I'm sorry I said that to him,
and I'm sorry I was happy
when his face turned purple.

06:49.508 --> 06:52.410
All right, Michael.
I understand.
You lost your temper.

06:52.478 --> 06:55.146
But that's no reason
to call daddy a liar.

06:55.214 --> 06:58.582
Gloria, I'm telling you,
Archie saw Tony being mugged!

06:58.650 --> 07:00.584
You didn't see him
see it, did you?

07:00.652 --> 07:03.287
Well, no, but--
then don't go around
accusing people.

07:03.355 --> 07:06.024
You're not always right.
You could be wrong, you know.

07:06.091 --> 07:08.393
It is possible.
You could be wrong.

07:08.460 --> 07:11.529
Just once
I'd like to hear you say,
"I could be wrong."

07:11.596 --> 07:13.531
All right.
I could be wrong.
Good.

07:13.598 --> 07:15.400
But not this time.

07:15.467 --> 07:18.503
[ Phone ringing ]

07:18.570 --> 07:21.539
Hello!
Excuse me. Hello.

07:21.606 --> 07:24.808
Just a minute, please.
Daddy, it's for you!

07:24.876 --> 07:28.479
[ Archie ]
Who is it?
Mrs. vicino!

07:28.547 --> 07:32.350
Geez, I don't wanna talk to her.
Did you tell her I was here?
Take a message.

07:32.418 --> 07:34.552
I'm sorry, Mrs. vicino.
He can't speak to you
at the moment.

07:34.619 --> 07:37.555
May I please take a message?
Shh, shh, shh!

07:40.025 --> 07:42.427
Oh.

07:42.494 --> 07:44.595
Uh-huh.

07:44.663 --> 07:46.597
Uh-huh.

07:48.434 --> 07:50.668
All right, Mrs. vicino.
Yes, I'll ask him.

07:50.735 --> 07:53.171
Yeah. Okay. Bye-bye.

07:53.238 --> 07:55.573
- What? What? What?
- Daddy, Mrs. vicino
wants to know...

07:55.640 --> 07:58.109
When you're going
to the police station
and tell them what you saw.

07:58.177 --> 08:01.412
You put a lid on that,
little girl. I told you
I didn't see nothing.

08:01.480 --> 08:05.583
- Daddy, you're lying.
- How dare you say
your father is lying!

08:05.650 --> 08:09.087
Because Mr. vicino
said that you were there
and saw everything.

08:09.154 --> 08:11.755
[ Groans ]
Archie, is that true?

08:11.823 --> 08:15.526
Listen, how could that shoemaker
be sure of what he's seen,

08:15.594 --> 08:18.963
after he fell down
on the sidewalk
and bumped his noggin there?

08:20.466 --> 08:22.833
You saw, arch.
You saw.

08:22.901 --> 08:25.035
If I was you,
I couldn't live with myself.

08:25.104 --> 08:28.439
Well, you ain't
living with yourself.
You're living with me.

08:32.677 --> 08:36.780
Michael, I apologize.
You were right.
Daddy, you lied to us!

08:36.847 --> 08:40.049
Listen, it ain't lying
to try to protect
yourself and your family.

08:40.119 --> 08:42.052
What?
If anything happened to me,

08:42.121 --> 08:44.355
this meathead couldn't keep you
in bubblegum.

08:44.423 --> 08:46.357
Oh, come off that bull, arch.

08:46.425 --> 08:48.926
What could happen?
It was just an ordinary mugging.

08:48.994 --> 08:50.828
"An ordinary little mugging,"
that's all.

08:52.097 --> 08:54.098
What do you know?
I was there.

08:54.166 --> 08:57.701
You didn't see nothing.
I seen it.

08:57.769 --> 09:01.472
Suppose I was to tell you
that that was done by
two mugs in blue silk suits...

09:01.540 --> 09:05.209
Riding in the back
of a big sedan that comes
screeching up to the curb?

09:05.277 --> 09:07.345
Come on, arch.
What are you trying to hand us?

09:07.412 --> 09:09.647
That's right.
There was a big black,

09:09.714 --> 09:11.849
probably bulletproof Cadillac
or something.

09:11.916 --> 09:13.784
Big bulletproof Cadillac?

09:13.852 --> 09:16.320
That's right.
You was in the store,
and you never seen it.

09:16.388 --> 09:18.756
Daddy, are you
trying to tell us
they were gangsters?

09:18.823 --> 09:22.793
Listen, little girl,
did you ever stop to think
of the kind of a name vicino is?

09:22.861 --> 09:25.796
Tony vicino? Antonio vicino?

09:25.864 --> 09:29.367
That's a nice name, Archie.

09:29.434 --> 09:31.369
It's musical.

09:31.436 --> 09:34.605
¶ Antonio vicino ¶

09:34.673 --> 09:38.342
stop that. Stop that.
Stop that. Stop that!
Stop that! Stop that!

09:43.148 --> 09:45.949
What I'm trying
to tell you is...

09:46.017 --> 09:49.720
That that is an Italian name--
vicino.

09:49.788 --> 09:52.890
It's worse than that.
It's a sicilian-Italian name.

09:52.957 --> 09:55.926
Are you trying to tell us that
the mafia is mixed up in this?

09:55.994 --> 09:59.897
Bingo, buddy. That's what
I'm trying to protect
me and my family against.

09:59.964 --> 10:03.668
I wanna tell you something.
Them sicilians
is famous for two things--

10:03.735 --> 10:06.837
spaghetti and revenge.
<i>[ Doorbell buzzing ]</i>

10:06.905 --> 10:10.140
Don't answer that door.
Get away from that door.

10:10.209 --> 10:12.142
I don't want you
talking to nobody.

10:12.211 --> 10:14.144
Now, stay over there.

10:16.147 --> 10:18.649
Mr. bunker?
Aw, geez.

10:18.717 --> 10:22.886
Listen,
I know what you're here for,
and I didn't see nothing.

10:22.954 --> 10:26.190
May I come in?
I'd just like to ask you
a few questions anyway.

10:26.258 --> 10:28.726
All right.
If you wanna, come on.

10:28.793 --> 10:31.962
I'll tell you up front
that I ain't no--

10:32.030 --> 10:34.532
what do you call--
a witness to that there event.

10:34.600 --> 10:38.836
That's right, officer.
Archie said he didn't
see no muggin'.

10:38.903 --> 10:40.838
He didn't see nothin',

10:40.905 --> 10:44.875
except a big
bulletproof Cadillac
from the mafia.

10:44.943 --> 10:46.877
Aw, geez!

10:49.748 --> 10:52.049
I think maybe
you'd better come with me
down to the precinct...

10:52.117 --> 10:54.918
And make a complete statement
to the detectives.

10:54.986 --> 10:58.556
Wait a minute, officer.
I'll tell you how
I couldn't have see nothin'.

10:58.624 --> 11:00.858
The mugger
was over here, see?

11:00.925 --> 11:02.926
I'm facing
in this direction here.

11:02.994 --> 11:04.928
You're facing
in that direction.
That's right.

11:04.996 --> 11:08.198
You know, like they say,
position is
nine-tenths of the law.

11:12.103 --> 11:14.037
Huh?
Yeah.

11:14.105 --> 11:17.475
See, the reason I'm doing that
is there's a wind
coming from this way.

11:17.542 --> 11:20.511
I'm standing facing this way
so I can light one of my cigars.

11:20.579 --> 11:23.981
Back here you said you
were out of cigars.
So what were you lighting?

11:24.048 --> 11:26.484
- Who said I was out of cigars?
- You did, arch.

11:26.551 --> 11:28.753
You told them
I went to get the cigars.

11:36.861 --> 11:39.029
You wanna get your coat,
Mr. bunker?

11:44.169 --> 11:46.671
Archie will be right back,
Mr. vicino.

11:46.738 --> 11:48.673
Sit down, won't you?

11:48.740 --> 11:51.709
Oh, Archie will be
so glad you're here.

11:51.777 --> 11:56.414
He was at the police station
last night for three hours.

11:56.481 --> 11:58.982
What a guy, huh?
A person like your Archie...

11:59.050 --> 12:01.819
Makes you feel real good
to belong to the human race.

12:01.886 --> 12:04.789
Yeah, maybe one of these days
we'll get him to join it.

12:06.458 --> 12:10.761
Nah, you young fellows
can take a lesson
from Mr. bunker. Get involved.

12:13.732 --> 12:18.402
I suppose that's why daddy took
so long at the police station,
'cause he was so involved.

12:18.470 --> 12:23.974
Oh, sure.
He said the police made him look
through 15 books of pictures,

12:24.042 --> 12:26.444
but none of them looked
like the two men.

12:27.579 --> 12:30.013
Two men?
In silk suits.

12:30.081 --> 12:33.451
- And a big car.
- What big car?

12:33.518 --> 12:35.453
Is that what he told the cops?

12:35.520 --> 12:39.590
[ Blubbers ]
It's as cold out there
as a well-digger's butt.

12:39.658 --> 12:41.592
Hey, bunker.

12:44.295 --> 12:47.665
- Vicino, what are you
doing here?
- Mr. vicino came over...

12:47.733 --> 12:50.300
To thank you
for going to the police.

12:50.369 --> 12:53.404
Oh. Well,
I'm glad for your--
what do you call--

12:53.472 --> 12:57.140
gratification and all that,
but I was only doing my duty.

12:57.208 --> 12:59.943
And drop in some other time.
Now, wait a minute.

13:00.011 --> 13:04.415
What's this about
a big car and two guys?
There was only one guy.

13:04.483 --> 13:07.084
Hey, what did you say?
He said he was just leaving.

13:07.151 --> 13:09.854
No, wait a second.
No car? Just one guy?

13:09.921 --> 13:12.556
No car.
Just one lousy punk.

13:12.624 --> 13:16.460
Here. I'll show you.
He comes around behind me
and grabs me like this, see?

13:16.528 --> 13:18.662
Yeah.
I can see
his leather jacket,

13:18.730 --> 13:20.698
but I can't see his face.

13:20.766 --> 13:25.168
But I can see bunker
standing there, staring
right at me and the mugger.

13:25.236 --> 13:28.138
- Then you did see it.
- You stay out of this.

13:28.206 --> 13:30.173
Do your homework
or something, huh?

13:30.241 --> 13:32.175
The kid's right.

13:32.243 --> 13:34.578
You saw.
I know you saw.

13:34.646 --> 13:37.615
Aw, you ain't got
no witnesses to that.

13:37.682 --> 13:39.817
<i>He</i> knows you saw.

13:41.720 --> 13:44.755
Oh, why are you
dragging him into this?

13:45.990 --> 13:47.991
He sees everything.

13:48.059 --> 13:50.861
He knows everything we do.
Get out of here.

13:50.929 --> 13:52.996
You don't really
believe that.
Yes, I do!

13:53.064 --> 13:55.599
Then how come youse people
are always running
to confession,

13:55.667 --> 13:57.601
telling him what's happening?

14:05.677 --> 14:09.079
- Daddy, you shouldn't say that.
- No, let him.

14:09.147 --> 14:11.715
Let him.
Now we're getting the truth.

14:11.783 --> 14:15.786
It's because I'm catholic
that you ain't helping me.

14:15.854 --> 14:18.456
That ain't the truth.
I'd say the same thing...

14:18.523 --> 14:20.491
Even if you belonged
to the right church.

14:23.361 --> 14:25.295
Aha!
Oh!

14:25.363 --> 14:27.731
Garlic, 100 proof.

14:29.634 --> 14:31.936
Oh, boy.
Oh, boy.
What? What?

14:32.003 --> 14:34.171
Oh, boy, oh, boy!
What? What?

14:34.238 --> 14:36.740
Michael, look at that.

14:36.808 --> 14:38.809
Oh, boy. Oh, boy!

14:38.877 --> 14:42.446
"Oh, boy! Oh, boy! Oh, boy!"
Come on. What is it?

14:42.514 --> 14:44.915
Read it, Gloria.

14:44.983 --> 14:48.018
"Mafia execution attempt.
Yesterday in queens,

14:48.086 --> 14:51.856
"members of the syndicate
allegedly made
an unsuccessful attempt...

14:51.923 --> 14:54.525
On the life
of shoe repairman,
Tony vicino."

14:54.593 --> 14:57.561
Oh, boy!
Oh, boy! Oh, boy!

14:57.629 --> 14:59.663
Don't you "oh, boy."
Go stand over by them.

14:59.731 --> 15:03.934
The mafia!
Now you're tying me
in with the mafia! Me!

15:04.002 --> 15:05.936
Wait a minute.
Listen to this.

15:06.004 --> 15:09.439
"Two mobsters in blue
silk suits were seen
speeding from the crime...

15:09.508 --> 15:13.076
By a Mr. Archie bunker
of 704 hauser street."

15:13.144 --> 15:16.446
Mama Mia, the mafia!
That's big trouble.

15:16.515 --> 15:18.682
Yeah, and Archie's
the one who's in it.

15:18.750 --> 15:20.885
Huh?
You know what
you've done, arch?

15:20.952 --> 15:23.353
You've fingered the mafia.
What are you talking about?

15:23.421 --> 15:26.323
You know how many people are
reading that? You know what the
circulation of that paper is?

15:26.391 --> 15:30.260
2,950,000.

15:30.328 --> 15:33.463
Will you stifle yourself.

15:33.532 --> 15:36.033
[ Phone ringing ]
Answer the phone.

15:36.100 --> 15:38.602
I don't want to talk.
I don't even want to know
who it is.
Hello.

15:38.670 --> 15:42.640
I can't get over it.
Only two men in history
have ever fingered the mafia--

15:42.707 --> 15:46.343
Joe villacci
and now Archie bunker.

15:46.411 --> 15:48.078
<i>[ Laughing ]</i>

15:48.146 --> 15:50.080
What's so funny?
What are you laughing about?

15:50.148 --> 15:53.651
Maybe you tying me in
with the mafia is gonna
cost me some business,

15:53.718 --> 15:57.721
but you know
what it's gonna cost you?
[ Mimics slashing sound ]

15:57.789 --> 16:00.991
I don't have to tie you in
with the mafia.

16:01.059 --> 16:03.727
You was born Italian.
I didn't tell you to do that.

16:03.795 --> 16:07.898
For every gangster, there are
millions of hard-working,
honest Italian people.

16:07.966 --> 16:10.200
Dummy up.
He's right.

16:10.268 --> 16:13.470
How would you like it if I say
just because you're stupid,

16:13.538 --> 16:15.673
all bunkers are stupid?

16:15.740 --> 16:17.675
Stupid bunker. Stupid bunker.

16:17.742 --> 16:21.745
Stupid bunker.
Stupid bunker number one.

16:21.813 --> 16:25.248
Now, that ain't right.
Isn't it better if I say,

16:25.316 --> 16:30.087
"nice bunker, nice bunker,
nice bunker, stupid bunker"?

16:32.857 --> 16:36.627
Don't you like that better?
Why don't you sit down,
Mr. vicino?

16:36.695 --> 16:39.763
I'll make some coffee.
Coffee?
What do you mean, coffee?

16:39.831 --> 16:42.700
I ain't running a diner here.
Who was that on the phone?

16:42.767 --> 16:45.903
I thought you said you
didn't wanna talk to nobody.

16:45.971 --> 16:49.139
That was before. I wanna know
who it was. I don't want
to be kept ignorant.

16:49.207 --> 16:52.142
I don't think you can change
at your age, arch.

16:52.210 --> 16:54.144
[ Laughing ]

16:54.212 --> 16:58.682
Pipe down
and dummy up, meathead.
Now, who was that?

16:58.750 --> 17:01.852
It was a Mr. Ralph silvestri.

17:01.920 --> 17:03.954
He's coming over
to talk to you.

17:04.021 --> 17:06.423
Well, who is Mr. silvestri?

17:06.491 --> 17:10.761
He said he was from
the pro-italia society.

17:10.829 --> 17:13.597
Oh, good night! Nice, Edith.
Don't you know what that is?

17:13.665 --> 17:17.267
What are you worried about?
It's just an Italian
antidefamation group.

17:17.335 --> 17:21.371
It's just another cover name
for the mafia.
That's all it is.

17:21.439 --> 17:25.142
You told silvestri
I'm here, Edith?
Don't you know what that means?

17:25.209 --> 17:29.013
The guy'll be probably
coming over here to give me
one of them eternal kisses.

17:32.316 --> 17:35.919
Why don't you leave town?
We can tell him you went
to visit your godfather.

17:39.090 --> 17:42.626
I don't think
Archie has a godfather.

17:45.797 --> 17:48.265
Edith, go to bed,
will you?

17:48.332 --> 17:51.468
But it's still morning.
Then sit down here!

17:56.607 --> 18:00.177
How am I gonna convince
them mafia torpedoes
it's all a mistake?

18:00.244 --> 18:02.179
Why don't you try
telling the truth?

18:02.246 --> 18:04.181
Wait a minute.
I got an idea.

18:04.248 --> 18:06.483
Hey, vicino,
you're Italian.

18:06.551 --> 18:09.119
That's a-what
my mama told me.

18:09.187 --> 18:12.923
All right.
Now, look, you gotta
talk to these guys, you see?

18:12.991 --> 18:15.592
I mean, they'll understand you.
You know their lingo.

18:15.660 --> 18:18.461
You know their hand signals
and everything there.

18:18.529 --> 18:21.965
There's only one hand signal
I know for the spot you're in.

18:22.033 --> 18:24.267
What's that?

18:24.335 --> 18:28.238
Aw, cut that out!
Vicino, be serious.

18:28.306 --> 18:32.676
Listen, you gotta tell the mafia
that it wasn't them
who did that muggin'.

18:32.744 --> 18:34.678
They'll believe it
comin' from you.

18:34.746 --> 18:36.980
One wop to another, huh?
Sure.

18:37.048 --> 18:39.616
No, no, no.

18:39.684 --> 18:41.585
I mean one human being
to another.

18:41.652 --> 18:43.587
Come on, vicino.
You gotta help me.

18:43.654 --> 18:46.690
Now you're asking me
for help, huh?
<i>[ Doorbell buzzing ]</i>

18:46.758 --> 18:49.893
Don't answer that.
That's that guy silvestri.

18:49.961 --> 18:51.995
Oh, come on, arch.
You're seeing too many movies.

18:52.063 --> 18:54.932
Mr. bunker?

18:54.999 --> 18:58.535
Oh, hiya there.
Hiya. Hiya. Hey, listen.

18:58.603 --> 19:00.570
It wasn't you guys that done
that muggin' at all.

19:00.638 --> 19:02.740
I was just telling that
to Tony vicino.

19:02.807 --> 19:05.242
Here's Tony
standing right over here.
Ain't that right, Tony?

19:05.309 --> 19:07.244
No <i>capisce.</i>

19:09.313 --> 19:14.684
[ Archie ]
Tony, where you going?
¶ arrivederci, bunker ¶

19:22.794 --> 19:26.663
I came out to check out
your story about a car
and two men in silk suits.

19:26.731 --> 19:29.299
There was no car,
no two men in silk suits,
nothin'.

19:29.367 --> 19:32.435
Then you lied, Mr. bunker.
Yeah, I lied.

19:32.503 --> 19:36.073
Archie, maybe that's
why he didn't kiss you.

19:41.312 --> 19:43.613
Don't help me, huh, Edith?

19:45.650 --> 19:48.886
I wanna thank you
for not doing that.

19:48.953 --> 19:50.888
I'll tell you
who done the muggin' though.

19:50.955 --> 19:53.223
It was a longhaired
blond kid.

19:53.291 --> 19:56.226
Now, this is the truth.
He didn't even look Italian.

19:56.294 --> 19:58.228
I think he was a German.

19:59.730 --> 20:02.299
He was tall, and he had
a black leather jacket on.

20:02.366 --> 20:04.367
A black leather jacket, huh?

20:04.435 --> 20:06.369
You're not gonna change
your story again, are you?

20:06.437 --> 20:10.473
No. No, no, no. That's
the story. This is it, I swear.
<i>[ Doorbell buzzing ]</i>

20:10.541 --> 20:12.876
Oh, hey,
that's our front doorbell.

20:12.944 --> 20:15.445
That means there's somebody
out there. Yeah.

20:15.513 --> 20:18.282
We got people coming in and out
of here all the time.

20:18.349 --> 20:21.318
You know,
what you call witnesses
to everything.

20:23.487 --> 20:25.189
Mr. bunker.
Yeah, what?

20:25.256 --> 20:27.657
I'm Ralph silvestri.

20:27.725 --> 20:29.659
We already got one.

20:31.062 --> 20:34.464
I mean, y-y-you're
Ralph silvestri?
Yeah.

20:34.532 --> 20:36.300
Then who are you?

20:36.367 --> 20:38.368
Detective sergeant Perkins.

20:38.436 --> 20:41.872
Detective sergeant Perkins?
Hey-hey!

20:41.940 --> 20:44.474
Hey, sergeant, I'm glad
to see you in the house.

20:44.542 --> 20:47.211
Hey, stay a while.
Ask me all the questions
you want.

20:47.278 --> 20:49.779
I'll talk to you later.
I don't want to keep you
from your friend.

20:49.848 --> 20:51.781
Oh, I wish you would,
sergeant.

20:51.850 --> 20:56.286
- Hey, listen, uh,
this here is Mr. silvestri.
- Ralph.

20:56.354 --> 21:00.557
Yeah, well, Ralph, uh,
look at this--

21:00.624 --> 21:02.726
sergeant Perkins
from the police.

21:02.793 --> 21:06.596
Excuse me, but I can't
stay long. I wanna talk
to you private. Come here.

21:06.664 --> 21:08.665
Come on, sergeant.
There ain't nothing private
in this house.

21:08.733 --> 21:11.201
I gotta get back
to the station.
Wait a minute.

21:11.269 --> 21:13.837
You can't leave me alone
with this here guy.

21:13.905 --> 21:15.839
Look, I can't
hang around here.

21:15.907 --> 21:19.609
But I want to see you tomorrow
down at the station
at 10:00 in the morning.

21:19.677 --> 21:22.479
What for?
To make
a complete statement.

21:22.546 --> 21:25.682
Now, get it clear
in your mind, bunker,
because under the law,

21:25.750 --> 21:28.718
you could be charged
with making a false statement
to a police officer.

21:28.786 --> 21:33.090
A false--
what could you get for that?
One year or $500.

21:33.157 --> 21:36.760
Oh, geez. Sergeant, wait
a minute. Hey, wait a minute.
Listen to me, sergeant.

21:36.827 --> 21:40.931
This guy silvestri here,
don't he worry you?

21:42.000 --> 21:45.168
Bunker,
get ahold of yourself.

