21:55.446 --> 21:58.048
Come here.

21:58.116 --> 22:02.152
We read about you
in the paper this morning.
Nice, huh?

22:02.220 --> 22:04.454
So we get a call from
one of the members in my club.

22:04.522 --> 22:07.291
He says, "ralphie,
you live in the neighborhood.

22:07.358 --> 22:10.327
Why don't you drop in
on Mr. bunker
and straighten him out?"

22:10.395 --> 22:12.495
Straighten me out?

22:12.563 --> 22:14.864
Your language.
[ Popping sound ]

22:14.933 --> 22:18.969
See, it reflects very bad
on the members of our club.

22:19.037 --> 22:23.006
Look, I'm talking about
that five-letter word
which begins with "m."

22:23.074 --> 22:26.343
Oh!
Am I making myself clear?

22:26.411 --> 22:29.446
Yeah, well, listen,
I don't think I ever
even heard of that word.

22:29.513 --> 22:32.449
Maybe I can help you.

22:34.419 --> 22:37.354
A five-letter word
beginning with "m"--

22:37.422 --> 22:42.159
Edith, the man ain't here
to play crosswords.

22:42.226 --> 22:45.795
Let me explain something to you.
I just dropped by to tell you...

22:45.863 --> 22:50.000
That that organization
which you mentioned
this morning in the paper,

22:50.068 --> 22:52.002
it don't exist.

22:52.070 --> 22:55.705
It's defunct.
Well, listen,
anything you say.

22:55.773 --> 22:57.941
We don't say that word.

22:58.009 --> 23:00.277
It's not a very nice word.

23:00.345 --> 23:02.645
You see, even in this movie,
the godfather,

23:02.713 --> 23:06.350
which is about that
defunct organization,

23:06.417 --> 23:08.352
even they don't use that word.

23:08.419 --> 23:11.821
I know the word. "Mafia."

23:13.491 --> 23:17.327
Lady, lady, even the FBI
don't use that word.

23:17.395 --> 23:19.762
You know what the FBI
calls organized crime?

23:19.830 --> 23:21.764
Organized crime.

23:23.267 --> 23:25.268
A better word.

23:25.336 --> 23:27.404
In that statement I made
to the police there,

23:27.472 --> 23:30.673
I didn't use no words
like "kosher nostras," see?

23:30.741 --> 23:33.643
Or that other mmm word.

23:33.711 --> 23:35.979
I ain't never gonna use
them words no more.

23:36.047 --> 23:37.981
Good, bunker.
That's all I wanted to know.

23:38.049 --> 23:40.317
I gotta go.
The wife and kids
are waiting in the car.

23:40.385 --> 23:43.953
Bye-bye, everybody.
[ Stammers, laughs ]

23:44.022 --> 23:46.823
Hey, by the by, the cop--

23:46.891 --> 23:50.827
you mentioned something
about a year in the can
and 500 bananas.

23:50.895 --> 23:53.163
That ain't gonna make you
change what you just said?

23:53.231 --> 23:55.365
No, no, no.
I told the truth just now.

23:55.433 --> 23:57.600
I mean,
I was honest this time.

23:57.668 --> 24:00.237
Good, bunker.
It pays to be honest...

24:00.304 --> 24:02.972
All the time.

24:03.041 --> 24:06.743
And remember, you heard it
from silvestri, huh?

24:06.810 --> 24:09.312
Bye-bye,
every beautiful people.

24:17.555 --> 24:20.757
Hey, Michael, you don't
really think the police
will put daddy in jail...

24:20.824 --> 24:22.759
For making
a false statement, do you?

24:22.826 --> 24:25.162
- I don't know. It's hard to s--
- <i>[ Gloria ] Daddy!</i>

24:25.229 --> 24:28.631
Archie, what happened?
They're not gonna put you
in jail, are they?

24:28.699 --> 24:31.234
What are you talking about,
put me in jail?

24:31.302 --> 24:33.836
Gee. They ain't even
gonna press no charges.

24:33.904 --> 24:36.506
That's wonderful.
Oh, good.

24:36.574 --> 24:39.109
- What happened?
- Oh, nothing much.

24:39.177 --> 24:41.344
You know that guy silvestri
that was here?

24:41.412 --> 24:43.547
Turned out
to be a pretty nice guy.

24:43.614 --> 24:46.450
Down at the station house
he put in a good word for me.

24:46.517 --> 24:50.554
Was it a five-letter word
beginning with "m"?

24:54.258 --> 24:58.761
You're a pip, Edith.
You know that? A real pip.

